      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation experiments must use the same pump geometry, fluid, and operating envelope as the COU. Any deviations must be formally justified.",
      "rationale": "Validation used the FDA generic pump geometry which matches COU geometry. However, validation fluid was saline-glycerol surrogate rather than blood analog, and operating range covered only 3 of 5 required flow-speed combinations. Achieved level 2 against required level 5."
    },
